15.84	Castel_dell'Ovo	Castel dell'Ovo	Castel dell'Ovo (in Italian, Egg Castle) is a castle located on the former island of Megaride, now a peninsula, on the gulf of Naples . The castle's name comes from a legend about the Roman poet Virgil, who had a reputation in medieval times as a great sorcerer, that he put a magical egg into the foundations to support the fortifications.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/19/Castel_dell-Ovo.JPG/300px-Castel_dell-Ovo.JPG
